  <p>
    <row>We roll a red $n1-sided die and a blue $n1-sided die. What is the probability that the sum of the two dice are $k1?</row>
    <answer><award><math simplify>(2$n1-$k1+1)/$n1^2</math></award></answer>
  </p>
  <p>
    <row>We roll a red $n1-sided die and a blue $n1-sided die. What is the probability that the sum of the two dice are $k2?</row>
    <answer><award><math simplify>(2$n1-$k2+1)/$n1^2</math></award></answer>
  </p>
  <p>
    <row>We roll a red $n2-sided die and a blue $n2-sided die. What is the probability that the sum of the two dice are $k3?</row>
    <answer><award><math simplify>(2$n2-$k3+1)/$n2^2</math></award></answer>
  </p>
  <p>
    <row>We roll a red $n2-sided die and a blue $n2-sided die. What is the probability that the sum of the two dice are $k4?</row>
    <answer><award><math simplify>(2$n2-$k4+1)/$n2^2</math></award></answer>
  </p>
